CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 2, 1958, pg. A12, reads: "The FROGS Have Fun - Frog Week opened last Sunday with a gay party for members, their wives and out-of-town guests at the Terrain Room of Terrace Hall.  The above pictures tell the story of how the Frogs and their guests had fun...  Lower left photo shows another happy group composed of, seated, left to right: Dr. R. W. Dixon, Mrs. Wendell Freeland, Mrs. James K. Lewis, Dr. Max Johnson, Frogs' president, and his wife.  Attorney Freeland, co-chairman with Robert Ratcliffe stand together with Dr. James K. Lewis. ... - All Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Dr. Reginald W. Dixon, Mrs. Freeland, Mrs. Lewis, Dr. Max Johnson and Mrs. Johnson seated, with Atty. Wendell Freeland Dr. James K. Lewis standing behind them, at FROGS week party in Terrain Room of Terrace Hall
